{
    "player_reason": "Decisive, ruthless — exactly the sort of action I respect. Killing the hag robs a manipulative creature of a bargaining chip, denies her the chance to return or flee with captives, and demonstrates strength rather than naive mercy. It suits my tastes and keeps us safer.",
